channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Utah judge to decide if author of book on grief will face trial in husband's death
item.description: An evidentiary hearing is set for a Utah woman who wrote a children’s book about coping with grief after her husband’s death and was later accused of fatally poisoning him

item.title: Israeli hardliner Ben-Gvir repeats call for prayer at Al-Aqsa mosque compound
Walmart recalls apple juice sold in 25 states due to arsenic concerns
item.description: Walmart has recalled nearly 10,000 cases of Great Value brand apple juice sold in stores across the U.S. due to potentially harmful levels of inorganic arsenic.

item.title: A dam collapses in Sudan after heavy rainfall. Local media report dozens missing
item.description: Sudan’s health ministry says a dam has collapsed due to heavy rainfall in the eastern Red Sea state, sending water flooding over nearby homes

item.title: Old US Bradleys becoming 'legend' in Ukraine shows what the country can do when it gets enough of the weapons it needs
Gunmen storm mystery shipwreck that triggered massive oil spill
item.description: The Gulfstream's ownership remains a mystery. The barge that had been towing it vanished, along with the crew.

item.title: Greek-flagged tanker is burning after Houthi attacks, but no sign of oil spill
item.description: A Greek-flagged tanker repeatedly attacked by Yemen’s Houthi rebels in the Red Sea remains ablaze but hasn’t sprung a major oil leak in the waterway

item.title: How North Palm Beach is growing: Twin City Mall plan calls for smaller buildings on U.S. 1
At least 23 people taken off vehicles and killed by gunmen in Pakistan
item.description: Officials in Pakistan's insurgency-plagued Baluchistan province say gunmen took 23 people off buses and trucks and gunned them down.

item.title: Fire engulfs apartment building in east London, sending 2 to hospital
item.description: Two people have been hospitalized after fire engulfed an apartment building in east London early Monday, sending thick black smoke into the air

item.title: 'Coward': Critics Mock Trump After Late-Night Freakout Over Kamala Harris Debate
Harris girds for battle with Trump over union workers and their Big Labor bosses
item.description: Democrats once had grip on blue-collar voters. Now, they must make their case to this key demographic that could play a decisive role in the election.

item.title: 1 dead as landslide sweeps across roads, into homes in Alaska, officials say
item.description: A landslide in Ketchikan, Alaska, blocked roads and damaged houses, killing at least one person, officials said.

item.title: Millions in this country are stranded by flooding. Many blame their neighbor
8/25: CBS Weekend News
item.description: Israel, Hezbollah exchange fire; Longtime CBS News correspondent Phil Jones dies at age 87
